# Testing And Quality Gates

- For feature and bug-fix work, write or update tests before finalizing implementation.
- Cover critical paths first: catalog browsing, product variants, cart, order draft creation, admin sync.
- Run relevant unit/integration tests and report what was executed.
- Never mark work complete with known failing checks in changed areas.
- Do not silently swallow errors; either handle, rethrow with context, or return a typed failure.

## Quality Checklist

- Functions are cohesive and readable; avoid deep nesting.
- File and symbol naming follows existing conventions.
- No duplicate logic if reusable utilities already exist.
- Edge cases explicitly handled: empty data, invalid IDs, timeout/fetch failures.
